The '''Electricity sector in [[South Africa]]''' is an important part of the economy in the region.
[[Eskom]] is the state-owned electricity provider.<ref>{{cite book|title=African Economic Outlook 2009 : Country Notes: Volumes 1 and 2|publisher=[[OECD Publishing]]|isbn=9789264076181|page=583|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=e91T-0zSWnAC&pg=PT585&dq=Electricity+sector+in+South+Africa+Eskom&hl=en&sa=X&ei=NLU8Ur-0K7P07Abc24HwDQ&ved=0CGUQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=Eskom&f=false|author=OECD, African Development Bank, United Nations Economic Commission for Africa|accessdate=20 September 2013|date=4 Dec 2009}}</ref> A 2016 study compared long term prices of different types of new powerplants.<ref>http://www.ee.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/New_Power_Generators_RSA-CSIR-14Oct2016.pdf</ref>

