{{Orphan|date=September 2015}}

'''Shower trains''' or '''bathing trains''' were specialized [[train]]s or [[train car]]s used throughout [[Europe]] to provide bathing facilities to troops stationed along the [[battlefront]] during the [[First World War]].

== Switzerland==
[[File:Armeebadezug - CH-BAR - 3240833.tif|thumbnail|left|The Swiss army shower train at a station.]]
[[File:Die Wasserleitung im Duschenraum des Armeebadezuges - CH-BAR - 3240838.tif|thumbnail|right|Shower room in a Swiss train.]]
Shower trains (known as '''''Armeebadezug''''') were used in [[Switzerland]]. Each train consisted of old [[rolling stock]] from private railway companies: a [[locomotive]], a [[tank car]] and converted [[Passenger car (rail)|passenger cars]], each with a shower room and two [[cloakroom]]s. The water was taken from the tank car and heated by the locomotive.

This train served the thousands of [[Swiss Armed Forces|Swiss militia]] protecting Switzerland's borders.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.drehscheibe-foren.de/foren/read.php?17,6339279|title= 04 - Historische Bahn|last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date=2013-03-24 |website=Drehscheibe Online |publisher= |language=German |trans-title=04 - Historic Path |accessdate=8 December 2013}}</ref>

== Imperial Russia ==
Similar bathing trains were used in the [[Russian Empire]] in 1914.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/btv1b69331711.r=train-bains.langEN|title= Inauguration d'un train-bain à Petrograd [novembre 1914 ?] : [photographie de presse] / [Agence Rol] |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=BNF Gallica|publisher= |language=French |trans-title=Opening ceremony of a bath train at Petragrad [November 1914?]: [Photography of the press] / [King Agency] |accessdate=8 December 2013}}</ref>

